Mechanical Designer (DMC/201404/03/SG)
Job ID
EPM-00007597
Country
Singapore
State/Province
Singapore
City
Singapore
Publish Start Date
Apr 28 2014
Job Level
Experienced (Non-Manager)
|
Responsibilities:
Prepare detail engineering drawings (General Arrangement, piping isometrics, structural detail etc.) and document meeting project requirements.
Liaise with fabricators/sub-contractors on mechanical design, construction drawings, piping design, adopting engineering best practices.
Work with engineers, project managers and team members in generating document in accordance with project requirements.
Review and approve fabrication and detailed construction drawings.
Prepare as-built drawings and compile final documentation.
Provide support to sales and proposal team during project pursuit.
Other duties as assigned by the supervisor or functional manager.
Requirements:
Diploma in Mechanical Engineering or related discipline.
Conversant with AutoCad, CadWorx and 3D modelling software.
Basic knowledge of piping/structural design, weld interpretation, API, ASME and ASTM standard.
Ability to interpret P&I diagram and understand equipment and drawing symbols.
Familiar with piping and steel structural materials.
Must be self-motivated, interpersonal savvy, customer focus and driven for results.